org.sakaiproject.entitybroker.impl

Class EntityBrokerCoreServiceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sakaiproject.entitybroker.impl.EntityBrokerCoreServiceManager

  • public class EntityBrokerCoreServiceManager
extends Object
    This allows easy startup of the core entitybroker services in a way which avoids the developer having to know anything about it, anyone who wants to startup the entitybroker core would create an instance of this class Note that the DeveloperHelperService has to be started separately
    Author:
    Aaron Zeckoski (azeckoski @ gmail.com)

      • EntityBrokerCoreServiceManager

        public EntityBrokerCoreServiceManager(EntityBrokerDao dao,
                              boolean useSpringBasedServices)
        Create the core services, set the optional dao so that the storage parts of EB work, enable the classes that depend on spring
        Parameters:
        dao - (optional) the dao which is used to write storage, without this the internal entityMetaPropertiesService and entityTaggingService will be null
        useSpringBasedServices - if true then spring impls will be used (must have spring classes in path)
